---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service | Moonraker" description="The terms that apply when you use moonraker.ai, including acceptable use, intellectual property, disclaimers, and limitation of liability." canonical="https://moonraker.ai/terms" ogTitle="Terms of Service | Moonraker" ogDescription="The terms that apply when you use the Moonraker website." ogUrl="https://moonraker.ai/terms">
<main>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-kicker">Terms of Service</div>
      <h1>The basics of using this site.</h1>
      <p>These terms apply when you visit or use moonraker.ai (the "Site"), operated by Moonraker AI ("Moonraker," "we," "us," or "our"). Please read them. By using the Site, you agree to these terms.</p>
      <div class="legal-meta">Last updated: June 4, 2026</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="legal-toc">
      <strong>On this page</strong>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="#accept">Accepting these terms</a></li>
        <li><a href="#site">What this site is</a></li>
        <li><a href="#use">Using the site</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ip">Our content and intellectual property</a></li>
        <li><a href="#third">Third-party links and content</a></li>
        <li><a href="#results">No professional advice or guaranteed results</a></li>
        <li><a href="#asis">Disclaimers</a></li>
        <li><a href="#liability">Limitation of liability</a></li>
        <li><a href="#law">Governing law</a></li>
        <li><a href="#changes">Changes to these terms</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contact">How to contact us</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="accept">1. Accepting these terms</h2>
    <p>By visiting, browsing, or otherwise using the Site, you agree to these terms and to our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.</p>

    <h2 id="site">2. What this site is</h2>
    <p>The Site provides information about Moonraker and the services we offer to therapy practices. Nothing on the Site is an offer or a binding agreement to provide services. Any work we do for a client is governed by a separate written agreement between Moonraker and that client. If there is a conflict between these terms and a signed client agreement, the signed agreement controls for that engagement.</p>

    <h2 id="use">3. Using the site</h2>
    <p>You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes. You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the Site in any way that breaks the law or infringes someone else's rights.</li>
      <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Site, its servers, or any connected systems.</li>
      <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Site, introduce malicious code, or place an unreasonable load on it.</li>
      <li>Scrape, copy, or republish substantial portions of the Site for a competing commercial purpose without our written permission.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="ip">4. Our content and intellectual property</h2>
    <p>The content on the Site, including text, design, graphics, logos, and the "CORE Marketing System" name and framework, is owned by Moonraker or used with permission, and is protected by intellectual property laws. You may view and share links to the Site for personal or internal business use. You may not copy, sell, republish, or create derivative works from our content for commercial use without our written permission.</p>

    <h2 id="third">5. Third-party links and content</h2>
    <p>The Site may link to or embed content from third parties, such as videos, podcasts, scheduling tools, and partner websites. We do not control that content and are not responsible for it. Your use of any third-party platform is governed by that platform's own terms and privacy policy.</p>

    <h2 id="results">6. No professional advice or guaranteed results</h2>
    <p>Information on the Site is general and for educational purposes. It is not medical, legal, financial, HIPAA, or compliance advice, and it should not be relied on as a substitute for advice from a qualified professional. Marketing and visibility results depend on many factors outside our control, including your market, location, specialty, and starting point. We do not guarantee specific rankings, traffic, inquiries, or revenue. Any specific guarantee that applies to a client engagement will be stated in that client's written agreement.</p>

    <h2 id="asis">7. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>The Site is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error free, or free of harmful components.</p>

    <h2 id="liability">8. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, Moonraker and its owners, employees, and contractors will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or inability to use, the Site. Where liability cannot be excluded, our total liability for any claim relating to the Site is limited to one hundred US dollars (US$100).</p>

    <h2 id="law">9. Governing law</h2>
    <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules. Any dispute relating to the Site that is not resolved informally will be handled in the state or federal courts located in Massachusetts, and you agree to that venue.</p>

    <h2 id="changes">10. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Your continued use of the Site after an update means you accept the revised terms.</p>

    <h2 id="contact">11. How to contact us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:chris@moonraker.ai">chris@moonraker.ai</a>.</p>

    <div class="legal-note">These terms are provided for general information and are not legal advice. We recommend reviewing them with your own qualified advisor before relying on them for your business.</div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="cta-inner">
      <div><h2>Ready to talk?</h2><p>Book a free strategy call and we will look at how Google and AI tools see your practice today.</p></div>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/free-strategy-call">Book a Free Strategy Call</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
.legal-hero { position: relative; overflow: hidden; background: linear-gradient(158deg, var(--color-navy) 0%, var(--color-navy-deep) 100%); color: var(--color-on-navy-dim); padding: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 5rem) 2rem clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3rem); }
.legal-hero .hero-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; display: block; max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
.hero-kicker { color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 800; font-size: .78rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; margin-bottom: .8rem; }
.legal-hero h1 { color: var(--color-on-navy); font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 4.5vw, 3.6rem); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.legal-hero p { color: var(--color-on-navy-dim); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; }
.legal-meta { margin-top: 1.1rem; font-size: .85rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
.legal-body { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.75rem) 2rem clamp(4rem, 7vw, 6rem); }
.legal-body h2 { font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.8rem); margin: 2.25rem 0 .85rem; letter-spacing: -.01em; }
.legal-body h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
.legal-body p, .legal-body li { color: var(--color-body); line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1rem; }
.legal-body p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.legal-body ul { list-style: none; display: grid; gap: .6rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
.legal-body li { padding-left: 1.2rem; position: relative; }
.legal-body li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: .68em; width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); }
.legal-body a { color: var(--color-primary); }
.legal-toc { background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-hairline); border-radius: var(--r-lg); padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-card); }
.legal-toc strong { display: block; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; margin-bottom: .7rem; color: var(--color-heading); }
.legal-toc ol { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; display: grid; gap: .35rem; }
.legal-toc a { color: var(--color-body); text-decoration: none; }
.legal-toc a:hover { color: var(--color-primary); }
.legal-note { background: var(--color-primary-subtle); border: 1px solid var(--color-primary-light); border-radius: var(--r-md); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-size: .92rem; color: var(--color-body); margin: 1.5rem 0; }
.cta-band { position: relative; overflow: hidden; background: linear-gradient(158deg, var(--color-navy) 0%, var(--color-navy-deep) 100%); color: var(--color-on-navy-dim); }
.cta-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem) 2rem; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; gap: 2rem; align-items: center; }
.cta-inner h2 { color: var(--color-on-navy); margin-bottom: .6rem; }
.cta-inner p { color: var(--color-on-navy-dim); }
@media (max-width: 860px) { .cta-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
